# UI: Naive UI

All new UI work MUST use [Naive UI](https://www.naiveui.com/) components. Do not
introduce raw HTML form controls, ad-hoc modals, or other component libraries for
new features.

## Setup (already configured)

- Package: `naive-ui`
- Auto-import: `unplugin-vue-components` + `NaiveUiResolver` in `vite.config.ts`
- Composables auto-imported: `useMessage`, `useDialog`, `useNotification`,
  `useLoadingBar`
- Root providers in `App.vue`: `NConfigProvider`, `NMessageProvider`, etc.

Use components directly in templates (no manual import needed). Prefer
`n-*` kebab-case tags in templates (e.g. `<n-button>`, `<n-input>`).

## Rules

- **Buttons**: `NButton` — not plain `<button>` (except inside Naive wrappers if needed).
- **Forms**: `NForm`, `NFormItem`, `NInput`, `NSelect`, `NCheckbox`, `NSwitch`, etc.
- **Feedback**: `useMessage()`, `useDialog()`, `useNotification()`, `useLoadingBar()`.
- **Layout**: `NSpace`, `NGrid`, `NLayout`, `NCard`, `NDivider`.
- **Data display**: `NDataTable`, `NTag`, `NBadge`, `NEmpty`.
- **Navigation**: `NMenu`, `NTabs`, `NBreadcrumb` (with Vue Router as needed).
- **Overlays**: `NModal`, `NDrawer`, `NPopover`, `NTooltip` — not custom CSS modals.
- **Icons**: `@vicons/*` packages when Naive UI examples use icons; match existing
  project icon choices if any are added later.

Tailwind CSS remains for page layout, spacing utilities, and one-off styling.
Prefer Naive UI props and theme tokens for component appearance.

## Examples

### Good

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
const message = useMessage()

function onSave() {
  message.success('Saved')
}
</script>

<template>
  <n-card title="Settings">
    <n-form>
      <n-form-item label="Name">
        <n-input placeholder="Your name" />
      </n-form-item>
    </n-form>
    <n-space>
      <n-button type="primary" @click="onSave">Save</n-button>
      <n-button quaternary>Cancel</n-button>
    </n-space>
  </n-card>
</template>
```

### Bad — avoid for new features

```vue
<template>
  <button class="rounded bg-blue-500 px-4 py-2 text-white" @click="save">Save</button>
  <input v-model="name" class="border p-2" />
</template>
```

